Trade Routes.Trade Way:
Extending in both directions, this major trading route led to both [[Baldur's Gate]] to the north and [[Calimport]] to the south

Traveling towards the north was difficult, as the soft river bottom made it hard to build bridges. Travelers had to either pay a barge to get them on the other side, or take a long detour (usually towards the east).{{Cite web|url= https://twitter.com/TheEdVerse/status/1538877066896191493 |title= Ed Greenwood on Twitter |accessdate=2022-06-21 |author= [[Ed Greenwood]] |authorlink= |coauthors= |date=2020-06-20 |year=2022 |month=06 |format= |work= |publisher= |pages= |language= |archiveurl= |archivedate= |quote= }}

