Government.Heraldry:
Two different symbols were used to represent the city:
* The simplest and most usual one was the [[wagon]]-on-barge. It was stamped on the badges signaling animals belonging to tax-payers, and was displayed on the city guard's [[tabard]]s.
* A more complex heraldry figured a thick horizontal blue line on a white background, on which three eight-spoked wagon wheels were centered&mdash;the central one overlapping the outer two. The blue bar represented the river, whereas the overlapping wheels represented caravan trade.{{Cite web/Candlekeep forum/Questions for Ed Greenwood (2010)/Heraldry of Crimmor and Athkatla}}
